.TH UNITFY 1 "April 2026" "unitfy 1.0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
unitfy \- command-line unit conversion utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B unitfy
.RI [ --version ]
.br
.B unitfy
.I value unit
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B unitfy
converts values between supported temperature, length, volume, and pressure units.
It can run in one-shot mode from command-line arguments or in interactive REPL mode when no arguments are provided.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --version
Print the program version and exit.
.SH REPL COMMANDS
.TP
.B help
Show usage and supported units.
.TP
.B exit
Exit REPL mode.
.TP
.B quit
Exit REPL mode.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B unitfy 100 celsius
Convert 100 Celsius to other supported temperature units.
.TP
.B unitfy 1 atm
Convert 1 atmosphere to other supported pressure units.
.TP
.B unitfy "12 fl oz"
Convert 12 fluid ounces to other supported volume units.
.TP
.B unitfy
Start interactive REPL mode.
.SH SUPPORTED UNIT FAMILIES
.TP
.B Temperature
C, F, K, R (and full names)
.TP
.B Length
mm, cm, m, km, in, ft, usft, ukft, mi
.TP
.B Volume
mL, L, gal, fl oz, m3, mm3, cm3
.TP
.B Pressure
Pa, kPa, bar, atm, psi, torr, mmHg
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.delta_history
Readline history file used by REPL mode when built with readline support.
